unify /ˈjuːnɪˌfaɪ/

(unifying,unified,unifies) 

1. V-T/V-I If someone unifies different things or parts, or if the things or parts unify , they are brought together to form one thing. 使成一体; 成为一体 

例： He pledged to unify the city's political factions. 他保证要统一全市的政治小集团。 

例： ...constitutional reforms designed to unify the country. …旨在统一国家的宪法改革。 

2. unified ADJ 统一的 

例： ...a unified system of taxation. …统一的税制。

